HEADWORD: Hunks
<hw>Hunks</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A covetous, sordid man; a miser; a
niggard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pray make your bargain with all the prudence and selfishness of an
old <qex>hunks</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunky</ent>⟦br⟧
